               <provenance>According to Additio 2, Särṣä ʾAragāwi bought
                     the Ms. and donated it to the church of Dabra Sahǝl Mikāʾel Bet Mäḵaʿ. The
                     names of his relatives are also mentioned: his father Zarʾa Krǝstos, his mother
                     Walatta Māryām, his wife ʿĀmata Māryām and his son Gabra ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer (s. also
                     the supplication formula on 194rb, and
                     Additiones 5 and 6). The original owner of the Ms. is not known.
                     In Additio 5, the name of Särṣä ʾAragāwi is written in a secondary hand over an
                     erasure where the original commissioner's/donor's name (?) might have stood
                     before.</provenance></history>
